1
00:00:06,877 --> 00:00:11,314
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

2
00:00:11,381 --> 00:00:14,908
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

3
00:00:14,985 --> 00:00:18,421
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

4
00:00:18,488 --> 00:00:22,083
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh! Just go my way</i>

5
00:00:22,159 --> 00:00:25,424
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

6
00:00:25,495 --> 00:00:27,429
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>

7
00:00:29,232 --> 00:00:32,167
<i>Down a difficult road</i>
<i>filled with endless struggles</i>

8
00:00:32,235 --> 00:00:36,035
<i>Where do you think you are going</i>
<i>following someone else's map?</i>

9
00:00:36,439 --> 00:00:43,277
<i>An insightful crow comes along</i>
<i>to tear up the map</i>

10
00:00:43,513 --> 00:00:50,578
<i>Now open your eyes and</i>
<i>take a look at the truth (Yeah!)</i>

11
00:00:50,887 --> 00:00:57,019
<i>There's nothing to lose,</i>
<i>so let's GO!!!</i>

12
00:00:57,160 --> 00:01:01,426
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

13
00:01:01,498 --> 00:01:05,093
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

14
00:01:05,168 --> 00:01:08,501
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

15
00:01:08,572 --> 00:01:12,201
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh!</i>
<i>Just go my way</i>

16
00:01:12,275 --> 00:01:15,870
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

17
00:01:15,946 --> 00:01:19,438
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best!</i>

18
00:01:19,516 --> 00:01:23,111
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

19
00:01:23,186 --> 00:01:27,282
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best! BANG!</i>

20
00:01:30,571 --> 00:01:33,199
Okay! Let's go!

21
00:01:39,513 --> 00:01:40,309
Huh?

22
00:01:45,886 --> 00:01:48,218
"Let's go,"
with so much energy...

23
00:01:48,289 --> 00:01:50,382
Don't act like a little kid!

24
00:01:51,058 --> 00:01:53,356
Oh? You're in a bad mood.

25
00:01:53,627 --> 00:01:56,528
Because! Because!
It's in the middle of my training!

26
00:01:56,597 --> 00:01:58,724
There are three steps
in the training, right?!

27
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:02,501
I'm only done with the second step!

28
00:02:04,271 --> 00:02:07,138
You can do the third step
even while walking.

29
00:02:07,441 --> 00:02:09,136
What! Really?!

30
00:02:13,681 --> 00:02:14,511
A balloon?

31
00:02:15,015 --> 00:02:15,845
Here!

32
00:02:21,989 --> 00:02:24,787
What's this...?
An ordinary balloon?

33
00:02:26,861 --> 00:02:31,924
The first step is "Spin."
The second step is "Power."

34
00:02:34,368 --> 00:02:38,270
And finally, the third step is this.

35
00:02:39,440 --> 00:02:43,171
<i>An lmpossible Choice.</i>
<i>The Pain Within Tsunade's Heart</i>

36
00:03:05,232 --> 00:03:07,393
Which one is "this"?!

37
00:03:09,136 --> 00:03:12,594
Watch me, it looks as if
I am simply holding a balloon...

38
00:03:12,807 --> 00:03:17,244
You say it "looks as if,"
but nothing is really happening.

39
00:03:17,344 --> 00:03:21,303
Then, I will do the same thing
on my left hand.

40
00:03:23,451 --> 00:03:26,682
Let's see what's really happening
inside the balloon.

41
00:03:30,925 --> 00:03:31,914
<i>Wow!</i>

42
00:03:31,992 --> 00:03:34,756
<i>The Chakra is randomly spinning</i>
<i>and going faster and faster...</i>

43
00:03:35,229 --> 00:03:39,461
<i>But still, it's perfectly round...</i>
<i>It's almost like...</i>

44
00:03:40,067 --> 00:03:42,228
Like a small typhoon, right?

45
00:03:44,371 --> 00:03:46,999
What's happening in your left hand...

46
00:03:47,341 --> 00:03:49,400
is happening inside that balloon
in your right hand, too?

47
00:03:49,877 --> 00:03:52,675
Yeah! That's right.

48
00:03:54,648 --> 00:03:55,979
<i>Cool...</i>

49
00:03:56,984 --> 00:04:02,479
<i>The balloon isn't moving at all</i>
<i>even if he's spinning that much Chakra...</i>

50
00:04:03,324 --> 00:04:06,054
<i>There's more power than</i>
<i>that time the rubber ball popped,</i>

51
00:04:06,126 --> 00:04:08,060
<i>and it's spinning a lot more too!</i>

52
00:04:08,562 --> 00:04:10,928
Listen, in this third step,

53
00:04:10,998 --> 00:04:13,796
you've got to use 100% of
what you have learned...

54
00:04:13,868 --> 00:04:15,529
and retain them.

55
00:04:18,706 --> 00:04:22,972
In other words, while keeping
the "Spin" and the "Power" at their max,

56
00:04:23,544 --> 00:04:26,775
imagine creating a single layer
within the balloon

57
00:04:27,014 --> 00:04:29,710
and compressing the Chakra within it.

58
00:04:34,021 --> 00:04:35,682
Got it!

59
00:04:36,190 --> 00:04:37,885
So, this training is about keeping

60
00:04:37,958 --> 00:04:40,051
the spin and power that I did
in the second step,

61
00:04:40,127 --> 00:04:43,096
and conversely,
trying not to pop a delicate balloon!

62
00:04:43,163 --> 00:04:46,621
Oh! That's the most perceptive
you've been so far!

63
00:04:48,269 --> 00:04:49,031
Huh?

64
00:04:49,470 --> 00:04:53,497
But, what's the point in going
to all the trouble?!

65
00:04:56,143 --> 00:04:58,043
In short, it means this.

66
00:04:59,613 --> 00:05:03,709
Watch! It's like this up until
the second step of the training.

67
00:05:15,429 --> 00:05:19,058
Next, after you have mastered
the third step!

68
00:05:29,510 --> 00:05:30,499
This is what happens!

69
00:05:49,363 --> 00:05:53,299
If you can keep this small typhoon
the size of your palm,

70
00:05:53,367 --> 00:05:54,891
the force won't disperse.

71
00:05:55,202 --> 00:05:57,432
The spinning gets faster and faster

72
00:05:57,504 --> 00:05:59,495
and the power gets
more and more compressed.

73
00:06:00,908 --> 00:06:04,571
And the destructive power
will reach its max.

74
00:06:07,448 --> 00:06:09,075
Well, so, that's that.

75
00:06:14,021 --> 00:06:16,489
<i>All right! I'll do this, too!</i>

76
00:06:33,474 --> 00:06:36,466
<i>Okay, this feels right...</i>

77
00:06:42,650 --> 00:06:43,480
<i>Now!</i>

78
00:06:43,951 --> 00:06:46,044
<i>Retain it here!</i>

79
00:06:47,688 --> 00:06:48,882
<i>Retain...</i>

80
00:06:56,563 --> 00:06:58,121
<i>Retain...</i>

81
00:07:03,170 --> 00:07:05,001
No cutting-corners!

82
00:07:05,406 --> 00:07:09,137
You've got to put out 100% spin and power,
and retain them.

83
00:07:09,710 --> 00:07:10,734
<i>You gotta be kidding...</i>

84
00:07:11,779 --> 00:07:16,341
<i>Unless I can perfectly control all my power,</i>
<i>it's impossible!</i>

85
00:07:19,887 --> 00:07:21,286
<i>Now I can see it...</i>

86
00:07:21,922 --> 00:07:23,583
<i>This third step...</i>

87
00:07:24,258 --> 00:07:26,658
<i>It's on a totally different level</i>
<i>compared to the others.</i>

88
00:07:26,994 --> 00:07:28,325
I told you...

89
00:07:28,562 --> 00:07:32,794
With an achievement difficulty of Rank A,
it's a super advanced Ninjutsu.

90
00:07:35,235 --> 00:07:40,002
Well, I'm done explaining!
We'll continue as we go on walking.

91
00:07:41,675 --> 00:07:43,233
Hey, hey!

92
00:07:43,677 --> 00:07:46,441
We don't need to rush so much,
until I can properly...

93
00:07:46,513 --> 00:07:50,279
We have already wasted enough time
waiting for your body to recover.

94
00:07:51,785 --> 00:07:55,778
There's no guarantee that
Tsunade stays in this town much longer.

95
00:07:56,023 --> 00:07:57,422
What?!

96
00:07:57,491 --> 00:07:58,856
But, but...

97
00:07:59,059 --> 00:08:01,755
It's not like an old acquaintance
is going to conveniently pop up

98
00:08:01,829 --> 00:08:04,559
and start talking about
the good old times with her...

99
00:08:05,232 --> 00:08:06,290
Come on, let's go!

100
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:08,094
All right...

101
00:08:46,707 --> 00:08:50,143
Long time no see... Orochimaru.

102
00:08:51,745 --> 00:08:54,441
I'd looked for you everywhere.

103
00:08:54,515 --> 00:08:57,040
What do you want from me
after so long a time?

104
00:08:57,918 --> 00:09:00,443
You aren't thinking of talking
about the old days...?

105
00:09:01,855 --> 00:09:05,450
Actually, I need to ask you
for a little favor...

106
00:09:07,327 --> 00:09:08,555
<i>His heartbeat is fast...</i>

107
00:09:09,329 --> 00:09:11,263
<i>From that complexion,</i>
<i>he must have a high fever.</i>

108
00:09:11,465 --> 00:09:13,365
<i>He must have been fatigued</i>
<i>for quite some time...</i>

109
00:09:14,067 --> 00:09:15,466
<i>And that arm...</i>

110
00:09:18,806 --> 00:09:19,568
Lady Tsunade.

111
00:09:21,375 --> 00:09:23,366
You must have understood by now.

112
00:09:23,877 --> 00:09:27,677
Go to someone else,
I don't treat anyone any more.

113
00:09:28,415 --> 00:09:29,575
That won't do...

114
00:09:30,851 --> 00:09:33,319
You must know how serious
this wound is...

115
00:09:34,121 --> 00:09:36,282
No one can treat this wound.

116
00:09:37,958 --> 00:09:40,324
Except for one of the Legendary Sannin

117
00:09:40,394 --> 00:09:43,454
who won her fame as
a medical specialist, Princess Tsunade...

118
00:09:44,298 --> 00:09:45,629
You...

119
00:09:50,304 --> 00:09:53,796
That arm...
it's not an ordinary wound.

120
00:09:57,277 --> 00:09:59,472
<i>A special Sealing Jutsu or something...?</i>

121
00:10:00,581 --> 00:10:02,276
What have you done?

122
00:10:03,550 --> 00:10:07,884
Well, it just happened...
when I killed the Third Hokage.

123
00:10:11,225 --> 00:10:13,716
You... Really?

124
00:10:14,194 --> 00:10:19,131
Humph. Don't look so scary.

125
00:10:20,067 --> 00:10:23,059
Anything that has a form
will one day decay...

126
00:10:23,637 --> 00:10:25,434
Same goes for humans.

127
00:10:31,511 --> 00:10:34,742
You must already know that too.

128
00:10:39,887 --> 00:10:46,918
For you have let two of
your most beloved ones die...

129
00:11:05,112 --> 00:11:09,048
<i>Let two of the most beloved ones die?</i>

130
00:11:10,584 --> 00:11:14,452
<i>I see... He thinks of terrible things.</i>

131
00:11:25,332 --> 00:11:30,031
That was a really terrible way to die...

132
00:11:30,337 --> 00:11:31,269
You!

133
00:11:41,548 --> 00:11:43,778
Poisoned...

134
00:11:47,554 --> 00:11:48,418
<i>She's fast!</i>

135
00:11:48,488 --> 00:11:49,477
Get out of my way!

136
00:11:49,957 --> 00:11:50,924
Won't let you!

137
00:11:53,226 --> 00:11:54,591
Calm down, Shizune!

138
00:12:10,177 --> 00:12:13,340
<i>This attendant...is an expert.</i>

139
00:12:24,591 --> 00:12:25,683
Orochimaru...

140
00:12:26,393 --> 00:12:29,658
Your personality's been like this
for a long time.

141
00:12:35,002 --> 00:12:37,436
And you know my personality
very well...

142
00:12:37,537 --> 00:12:39,596
So stop fooling around with me.

143
00:13:00,394 --> 00:13:02,794
I'll kill you, bastard!

144
00:13:04,431 --> 00:13:05,363
<i>She's powerful...</i>

145
00:13:07,267 --> 00:13:11,670
<i>And so scary...</i>
<i>she definitely must be single.</i>

146
00:13:13,940 --> 00:13:17,398
Tsunade is impatient and short tempered...

147
00:13:22,916 --> 00:13:25,680
Hey Naruto,
there's no time to be falling

148
00:13:25,852 --> 00:13:27,376
If we don't hurry,

149
00:13:27,454 --> 00:13:30,423
who knows where that shrew
will disappear again.

150
00:13:30,957 --> 00:13:32,584
Hey you, Pervy Sage!

151
00:13:32,659 --> 00:13:35,457
That's no way to speak to
a hard working apprentice!

152
00:13:35,629 --> 00:13:40,498
Shut up. Tsunade is the first priority now,
not you.

153
00:13:41,835 --> 00:13:44,497
Well, what the heck!

154
00:13:49,843 --> 00:13:53,609
<i>To have this Pervy Sage come</i>
<i>all the way to meet her...</i>

155
00:13:53,814 --> 00:13:56,305
<i>Who could this Kunoichi Tsunade be?</i>

156
00:13:59,719 --> 00:14:02,017
<i>Hope she's still here...</i>

157
00:14:07,260 --> 00:14:09,626
We didn't come here to fight.

158
00:14:10,564 --> 00:14:12,259
We just want to negotiate with you!

159
00:14:13,934 --> 00:14:14,901
Negotiate?

160
00:14:15,368 --> 00:14:16,130
Yes.

161
00:14:16,937 --> 00:14:18,495
Don't make me laugh!

162
00:14:22,709 --> 00:14:25,735
I've already told you once.
Get out of my sight!

163
00:14:26,413 --> 00:14:28,040
We can't do that.

164
00:14:29,316 --> 00:14:30,305
Get out of my sight.

165
00:14:31,017 --> 00:14:34,748
You are the only one
who can treat Lord Orochimaru's arm.

166
00:14:35,489 --> 00:14:36,478
Get out of my sight.

167
00:14:37,357 --> 00:14:39,018
We're not asking you to do it for free.

168
00:14:39,259 --> 00:14:40,521
Let's make a deal!

169
00:14:41,094 --> 00:14:44,586
I'll count up to five.
Leave before I'm done.

170
00:14:47,300 --> 00:14:50,167
Or else, I'll make you disappear myself.

171
00:14:50,537 --> 00:14:54,564
Please calm down.
It won't be a bad deal for you...

172
00:14:54,641 --> 00:14:55,471
Five...

173
00:14:57,677 --> 00:14:58,302
Four...

174
00:15:01,948 --> 00:15:02,573
Three...

175
00:15:05,218 --> 00:15:05,980
Two...

176
00:15:08,889 --> 00:15:09,617
One...

177
00:15:11,725 --> 00:15:16,594
I'll resurrect the little brother
and man, both of whom you loved...

178
00:15:20,667 --> 00:15:24,296
with the Forbidden Jutsu I've developed.

179
00:15:41,655 --> 00:15:45,591
Since we haven't disappeared yet,

180
00:15:47,527 --> 00:15:51,088
I'm guessing that the deal is made?

181
00:15:57,971 --> 00:16:00,872
Yes. I do know this young lady...

182
00:16:01,141 --> 00:16:02,005
Really?

183
00:16:02,242 --> 00:16:03,231
Yeah.

184
00:16:03,843 --> 00:16:06,744
To win back the money she lost here,
I think she said...

185
00:16:07,013 --> 00:16:08,947
she was going over there.

186
00:16:09,583 --> 00:16:11,312
Spin... Power...

187
00:16:11,384 --> 00:16:15,252
Letting them out to their max.
And retain it...

188
00:16:15,956 --> 00:16:17,218
Hey, kid.

189
00:16:17,591 --> 00:16:18,455
Hmm?

190
00:16:18,525 --> 00:16:21,050
Wanna gamble a bit, too?

191
00:16:21,661 --> 00:16:24,152
Over there? Where is that?

192
00:16:24,731 --> 00:16:25,459
Hmm?

193
00:16:26,433 --> 00:16:28,526
See, if the total number of the pips
on these dices

194
00:16:28,602 --> 00:16:30,160
comes out as even numbers,
that's Cho

195
00:16:30,237 --> 00:16:31,727
and if it's odd, that's "Han."

196
00:16:32,072 --> 00:16:36,406
Shut up! I am training right now,
don't bug me!

197
00:16:36,710 --> 00:16:39,110
What nonsense!
This is a gambling house.

198
00:16:39,613 --> 00:16:43,481
Instead of that balloon,
let's play with these.

199
00:16:43,550 --> 00:16:48,749
No way! I don't have any time
to be playing with those dice!

200
00:16:49,055 --> 00:16:50,647
Ha, what a boring kid!

201
00:16:51,091 --> 00:16:51,921
Shut up!

202
00:16:52,125 --> 00:16:54,355
So... can you tell me where that is?

203
00:16:54,461 --> 00:16:58,488
Well, you can't expect things to be free
in a gambling house, you know?

204
00:16:58,765 --> 00:16:59,891
Okay...

205
00:17:06,006 --> 00:17:10,272
Let's make a deal.
The information will be free if you win...

206
00:17:10,610 --> 00:17:13,306
And if you lose,
I'll give it to you for 1000 ryo.

207
00:17:13,413 --> 00:17:14,380
All right!

208
00:17:15,015 --> 00:17:16,983
So choose, odd or even!

209
00:17:17,050 --> 00:17:18,574
Okay! Here we go...

210
00:17:24,057 --> 00:17:28,494
<i>Well, so...</i>
<i>since I am exactly 50 years old.</i>

211
00:17:29,829 --> 00:17:30,727
I'll go for... even!

212
00:17:31,698 --> 00:17:33,666
If it's odd, I win...

213
00:17:34,434 --> 00:17:36,595
I'll open it now.

214
00:17:41,675 --> 00:17:44,166
<i>Oh no! 2 and 5, odd!</i>

215
00:17:46,780 --> 00:17:47,974
W-What the heck?!

216
00:17:48,481 --> 00:17:49,641
1000 ryo...

217
00:17:52,285 --> 00:17:53,809
<i>Nice, Naruto!</i>

218
00:17:56,089 --> 00:17:58,148
Looks like I won...

219
00:18:00,393 --> 00:18:03,829
<i>Darn! It didn't work again!</i>

220
00:18:06,933 --> 00:18:07,922
Retain...

221
00:18:11,838 --> 00:18:14,739
Where shall I look next?

222
00:18:26,586 --> 00:18:29,453
Geez, she's nowhere to be found!

223
00:18:38,898 --> 00:18:40,593
Hm? Me?

224
00:18:44,204 --> 00:18:45,330
Lotto?

225
00:18:45,805 --> 00:18:48,433
Kids, grownups, everyone loves it.

226
00:18:48,508 --> 00:18:50,669
Come and play with
this fun, fun Lotto.

227
00:18:51,911 --> 00:18:53,936
There's one that you know
the result right away.

228
00:18:54,013 --> 00:18:54,945
Which one do you want?

229
00:18:59,886 --> 00:19:03,754
Really, you are so much cuter
being chubby!

230
00:19:03,990 --> 00:19:07,517
<i>I can't believe he won</i>
<i>with just one draw.</i>

231
00:19:08,128 --> 00:19:10,858
<i>He's very talented in this...</i>

232
00:19:11,798 --> 00:19:14,460
<i>though his talent in Jutsu</i>
<i>is still immature.</i>

233
00:19:15,435 --> 00:19:17,699
<i>Well...anyhow...</i>

234
00:19:18,471 --> 00:19:20,496
<i>Where could have Tsunade gone?</i>

235
00:19:21,307 --> 00:19:24,936
<i>She couldn't have gone that far</i>
<i>in this short amount of time.</i>

236
00:19:27,080 --> 00:19:30,948
<i>I guess we'll have to</i>
<i>search for her from a higher place.</i>

237
00:19:31,751 --> 00:19:34,811
<i>If I remember it correctly,</i>
<i>this is a castle town.</i>

238
00:19:35,388 --> 00:19:37,447
<i>If we go up to the castle...</i>

239
00:19:37,724 --> 00:19:39,919
Naruto! This way!

240
00:19:50,970 --> 00:19:55,100
Don't you want to see those two...
Tsunade?

241
00:20:02,415 --> 00:20:04,815
<i>Nawaki...Dan...</i>

242
00:20:14,327 --> 00:20:18,354
If I treat your arms,
what do you intend to do with them?

243
00:20:23,169 --> 00:20:26,570
Well, I don't like to lie...

244
00:20:27,507 --> 00:20:30,840
So, I will tell you the truth.

245
00:20:36,883 --> 00:20:40,148
Hey, hey! Where is the castle?

246
00:20:45,191 --> 00:20:46,522
It's not there...?

247
00:20:49,295 --> 00:20:52,389
In addition to getting what I want...

248
00:20:58,338 --> 00:21:03,435
This time, I will completely destroy
the Leaf Village!

249
00:21:09,182 --> 00:21:13,118
<i>A cycle of hardship, right?</i>

250
00:21:14,121 --> 00:21:18,080
<i>Inside, we were crying, right?</i>

251
00:21:19,393 --> 00:21:27,357
<i>But the one thing we won't give up</i>
<i>is the dream we've chosen, right?</i>

252
00:21:28,335 --> 00:21:30,428
<i>It's a secondary role,</i>

253
00:21:33,206 --> 00:21:36,232
<i>a role in the shadows</i>

254
00:21:36,677 --> 00:21:41,614
<i>But in reaching for that dream,</i>

255
00:21:41,748 --> 00:21:47,209
<i>let us stay centered,</i>
<i>let us stay true</i>

256
00:21:47,387 --> 00:21:52,290
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we hung on without giving up</i>

257
00:21:52,359 --> 00:21:57,262
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we kept coming back up</i>

258
00:21:57,331 --> 00:22:06,501
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we believed and dreamed</i>

259
00:22:06,974 --> 00:22:11,843
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we've seen fools</i>

260
00:22:11,912 --> 00:22:17,748
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we've stood in the shadows of others</i>

261
00:22:19,386 --> 00:22:29,523
<i>Now, it's our turn...</i>
<i>Let us bask in our dreams</i>

262
00:22:37,437 --> 00:22:39,667
Hey, enough already!

263
00:22:40,007 --> 00:22:41,338
Who cares if she <i>is</i> one of the Sannin?!

264
00:22:41,408 --> 00:22:43,000
Who cares if she <i>is</i>
the legendary Kunoichi?!

265
00:22:43,176 --> 00:22:44,837
Who cares if she's
the medical specialist?!

266
00:22:45,212 --> 00:22:47,874
There's no way I'll accept
this person as the new Hokage!

267
00:22:48,248 --> 00:22:52,150
If she belittles the Third
and Fourth Hokages...

268
00:22:52,419 --> 00:22:54,649
I don't care if she's the candidate
to be the Fifth Hokage!

269
00:22:54,921 --> 00:22:57,082
I'll kick her butt!

270
00:22:58,091 --> 00:23:01,390
Next time:
"Unforgivable! A Total Lack of Respect!"
